The course contains following topics: social studies curriculum and syllabus analysis; social science-related instruction materials, implementation methodology; cross-curricular themes in social studies - teaching opportunities; analysis of the thematic blocks, analysis the teaching materials, project learning opportunities in civics education.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give the main theoretical knowledge's for teaching civics in lower and upper secondary school and to develop the abilities for working with the civics curriculum. Course units contains analyzing the social studies concept and content of the thematic material handling. During the course skills to work in civic education syllabus and methodological materials are formed. The course is in close relation to historical and social studies didactics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  To develop the following competencies:
Planning of teaching competence.
Literacy curriculum.
The thematic substance of competence.
Subject content and the structuring power of association.
Methods of implementation capacity.
Implementing cross curricular themes.
